The paper discusses the Bibliometric-enhanced Information Retrieval workshop series, which is focused on academic search and at the crossroads between Information Retrieval, Natural Language Processing, and Bibliometrics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the workshop series also covers topics related to Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), which could also be relevant sub-categories.
